<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 width="95%"><TR><td bgcolor="#F7F7F7"><TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="100%"><TR bgcolor="#9FA6C4"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000000" FACE="Verdana">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">jimbo</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">  I've got a great idea...how about me and a few people start up a guild that differs a little.<BR>  Forget the whole truth, happiness and good way of life(because most of the guild members just do whatever anyway...) and establish one for the great virtues. Like training each other to work as a team and exploring Norrath? This game is full of endless possibilities all you need do is look.<BR>  The guild would have to be small to work and prefferably the people would have a sense of having fun here, not go here and camp on the orcs for 10 hours straight and get that next lvl. Thats stuff better saved for soloing...<P>  If anyone is intrested give me an email or a tell.<P><BR> Nexs</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">gleewind</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">I was dabbling with an idea for a guild. Not dedicated to 'Hands across Norrath', though it would be indifferent to race. I was thinking of a research guild of scholars. People who know a lot of information about the different zones, different monsters, and different items. And would be able to provide the information to others... all someone would have to do is see if there are any members of the guild online and ask his question... and hopefully get an answer right away....<BR>  Sort of as a public service, saving people from having to camp, check this site, then come back. Wardens of Lore or some such name.<P><P>------------------<BR>Ibamn<BR>Brell Serilis<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Loozar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">sounds like a good idea.  i am not into role playing, but i don't want to discourage those who do role play.  i don't like camping for hours when i can be exploring new zones.  i usually prefer solo or groups of 2 or 3 sensible people.  i probably play conservative, because i abolutely hate walking all over looking for my corpse.  the most fun i've had in this game is when i group with two other people and we go to a new zone or fulfill a new quest.  i also enjoy helping others when i can.  if this is the kind of guild you're looking to form, i'd be interested in joining. <P>loozar<BR>11th season ranger </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#D9DCE8"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">nexs</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana"> Both of those ideas sound very intreating, sort of a break forom the "hands across Norrath" theme that we're seeing. If anyone else is intrested, let me know so we can get the ball rolling...<P>Nexs</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#E8EAF0"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">Lanthan</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana">That guild that Jimbo was talking about sounds interesting.  I'd like to sign up if you'll take a soon to be lvl 9 paladin.  I'm usually on at 9:30 pm EST</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></td></tr></table> 
